Singapore Caps Local Visitors to Casinos at 30%, Business Times Reports

-- B y   G l e n y s   S i m
-- 
2011-06-09T23:08:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-09/singapore-caps-local-casino-visitors-at-30-business-times-says.html
Las Vegas Sands Corp. (LVS)  has been told
to make sure not more than 30 percent of all casino visitors at
its Marina Bay Sands casino resort are Singaporeans, the
Business Times reported, citing President and Chief Operating
Officer Michael Leven.  The number of Singaporean visitors to the Marina Bay Sands’
casino has been about 30 percent, the newspaper said.  Operators have been told  Singapore  casinos are tourist
products and they aren’t to target the domestic market, the
report said, citing an unnamed Ministry of Community Development
spokesman, who didn’t confirm the 30 percent cap.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Glenys Sim in Singapore at 
 gsim4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sean Collins at 
 scollins14@bloomberg.net  